Alongside iOS 26.3, iPadOS 26.3, and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/macos-26/">macOS Tahoe</a> 26.3, Apple has released new <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/homepod/">HomePod</a> 26.3 software for the &zwnj;HomePod&zwnj; and the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/homepod-mini/">HomePod mini</a>. The update comes two months after Apple released &zwnj;HomePod&zwnj; Software 26.2. <br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2023/01/HomePod-2-and-Mini-feature-1.jpg" alt="" width="1600" height="900" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-882634" /><br/>
According to Apple's release notes, &zwnj;HomePod&zwnj; Software 26.3 includes performance and stability improvements.<br/>
<br/>
